\subsection{Projective image of an Artin representation}
\begin{definition}\label{artin.projective_image}
\uses{artin}
Composing an {{KNOWL('artin', 'Artin representation')}} $\Gal(\overline{\Q}/\Q)\to\GL_n(\C)$ with the natural projection $\GL_n(\C)\to\PGL_n(\C)$ gives a continuous homomorphism $\rho:\Gal(\overline{\Q}/\Q)\to\PGL_n(\C)$ with finite image.

The image of $\rho$ is the **projective image** of the Artin representation.
\end{definition}


